  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extension and associated rear terrace and balustrading by reason of their inappropriate detailed design, siting, scale, form and prominence would form a dominant and discordant addition to the existing characterful, legible and predominantly unaltered rear roofline of the host property and wider terrace. The extension would undermine the integrity of the terrace and would be clearly visible from short to longer views from several public and private viewpoints in and around the site. The proposal will fail to preserve and enhance the character and appearance of the Duncan Terrace/Colebrooke Row Conservation Area contrary to policies CS8 and CS9 of the Core Strategy (2011), policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of the Development Management Policies (2013), the Islington Urban Design Guide (2017), Islington's Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002) & THE NPPF 2019."
